K-9 Doctor Who

As depicted in the hit Doctor Who TV Franchise, in the year 5000, this robot was created by Professor Marius. Professor Marius was able to eradicate an alien virus with the assistance of the Doctor and Leela. After this, the Professor asked the Doctor to take care of K-9 as a companion robotic dog.

Doctor Who DIY K9 Model

The Metal Earth Doctor Who Model K9 Kit is a 3D detailed DIY kit laser cut from metal sheets by Fascinations, Metal Earth Australia. These hobby kits are miniature models that sparkle in the light and offer pleasant, enjoyable model building. Once finished, you can put the Doctor Who Robot Dog model on display in your home as a finely crafted museum miniature copy.

This 3D model comes in sheet form and can be easily constructed by removing the components from the metal sheets provided and connecting them using tabs and holes. No adhesive or soldering is necessary, but using tools such as tweezers and wire cutters can make the assembly process more manageable.

It is easy to assemble the parts and is recommended for ages 14+.

We offer free shipping on this Doctor who model; take advantage by ordering this kit for yourself!
